This paper deals with the sample complexity of PAC learning, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analysis and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) due to the potential implications of the results on the efficiency of learning algorithms and their applications in network analysis.
